cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about text generation using GANs, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach inspired by optimal transport, which involves optimizing a critic and an objective function, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper includes experiments on style transfer and unsupervised cipher cracking, which involve image processing and cryptography, respectively, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another possible sub-category.
